{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id52ee9009-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s2718"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2718"},"text":"§ 2718.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Interest on balances due department","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In suits for balances due the Post Office Department may recover interest at the rate of 6 per centum per year from the time of default.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id52ee900a-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/86/682/s9"},"text":"Pub. L. 86–682, § 9","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1960-09-02"},"text":"Sept. 2, 1960","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/74/708"},"text":"74 Stat. 708","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id52ee900b-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id52ee900c-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id52ee900d-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was derived from R.S. § 964, which was originally classified to section 788 of former Title 28. Following the general revision and enactment of Title 28 by act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1948-06-25"},"text":"June 25, 1948","children":[],"tail":", R.S. § 964 was reclassified to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t39/s846"},"tex